article.headline: Long Beach State 58, UC Riverside 56
article.story: LONG BEACH, Calif. (AP) -- Jibril Hodges tied a career-high with 24 points as Long Beach State defeated UC Riverside 58-56 Thursday. Hodges made 7 of 10 shots from the field, including five 3-pointers, as the 49ers (4-18, 2-10 Big West Conference) snapped a three game losing streak and won for only the second time in their last 13 games. Long Beach State beat Riverside for the first time in seven meetings. With 6.3 seconds remaining in the game, Ricky Porter missed a free throw that would have tied the game at 57. Instead, UC Riverside (3-8, 8-13) trailed by a point, 57-56. Onye Ibekwe was fouled as he rebounded Porter's miss and made one of two free throws to give the 49ers a 58-56 lead with 5.6 seconds left in the game. Porter took the inbounds pass and drove the length of the floor, but missed an off-balance 17-footer at the buzzer. Steve Williams had 17 points and 16 rebounds for the Highlanders. Porter added 14 for UC Riverside, which dropped to 2-9 on the road.
